  "prompt": "Which US Senate seats are up for reelection in 2018?",
  "response": "In the 2018 United States Senate elections, the following seats were up for reelection:\n\n1. Arizona (Jeff Flake - Republican)\n2. California (Dianne Feinstein - Democrat)\n3. Connecticut (Chris Murphy - Democrat)\n4. Delaware (Tom Carper - Democrat)\n5. Florida (Bill Nelson - Democrat)\n6. Hawaii (Mazie Hirono - Democrat)\n7. Indiana (Joe Donnelly - Democrat)\n8. Maine (Angus King - Independent)\n9. Maryland (Ben Cardin - Democrat)\n10. Massachusetts (Elizabeth Warren - Democrat)\n11. Michigan (Debbie Stabenow - Democrat)\n12. Minnesota (Amy Klobuchar - Democrat)\n13. Minnesota (Special election for Al Franken's seat, held by Tina Smith - Democrat)\n14. Mississippi (Roger Wicker - Republican)\n15. Mississippi (Special election for Thad Cochran's seat)\n16. Missouri (Claire McCaskill - Democrat)\n17. Montana (Jon Tester - Democrat)\n18. Nebraska (Deb Fischer - Republican)\n19. Nevada (Dean Heller - Republican)\n20. New Jersey (Bob Menendez - Democrat)\n21. New Mexico (Martin Heinrich - Democrat)\n22. New York (Kirsten Gillibrand - Democrat)\n23. North Dakota (Heidi Heitkamp - Democrat)\n24. Ohio (Sherrod Brown - Democrat)\n25. Pennsylvania (Bob Casey Jr. - Democrat)\n26. Rhode Island (Sheldon Whitehouse - Democrat)\n27. Tennessee (Bob Corker - Republican)\n28. Texas (Ted Cruz - Republican)\n29. Utah (Orrin Hatch - Republican)\n30. Vermont (Bernie Sanders - Independent)\n31. Virginia (Tim Kaine - Democrat)\n32. Washington (Maria Cantwell - Democrat)\n33. West Virginia (Joe Manchin - Democrat)\n34. Wisconsin (Tammy Baldwin - Democrat)\n35. Wyoming (John Barrasso - Republican)\n\nThese elections were part of the regular cycle, with senators serving six-year terms. Additionally, special elections were held in Minnesota and Mississippi due to resignations.",
